# Blog002 Architecture Plan

## 1) Module structure and file organization

Rust workspace (Issue #1) with two apps and one shared crate:
- `apps/api` (Axum backend)
- `apps/web` (Leptos frontend)
- `crates/shared` (shared DTOs, enums, validation-friendly types)

Top-level layout:
- `Cargo.toml` (workspace members + shared deps)
- `docker-compose.yml` (Issue #2)
- `.env.example` (document required runtime vars)
- `migrations/` (sqlx or refinery style migrations, Issue #3 onward)
- `infra/` (Dockerfiles + deploy config in Issue #26)

Backend (`apps/api/src`):
- `main.rs` (bootstrap)
- `config.rs` (env loading)
- `app_state.rs` (shared state: DB pool, S3 client, JWT config)
- `db/` (pool init, migration runner)
- `auth/` (`jwt.rs`, `middleware.rs`, `handlers.rs`)
- `modules/`
  - `categories/` (model/repo/service/handler)
  - `tags/`
  - `posts/`
  - `uploads/`
- `http/`
  - `routes.rs`
  - `error.rs` (central API error mapping)
  - `validation.rs` (shared input validators)
- `tests/` (integration tests, Issue #24)

Frontend (`apps/web/src`):
- `main.rs`
- `app.rs` (router shell)
- `api/` (typed client wrappers)
- `state/` (auth/session state)
- `pages/`
  - `admin/login.rs`
  - `admin/categories.rs`
  - `admin/tags.rs`
  - `admin/posts_list.rs`
  - `admin/post_form.rs`
  - `public/home.rs`
  - `public/post_detail.rs`
  - `public/filter.rs`
- `components/` (reusable form, editor, upload, pagination)
- `styles/` (Tailwind entry + theme tokens, Issue #4)

Shared crate (`crates/shared/src`):
- `dto/` request/response types used by API + frontend client
- `auth.rs` claims/session types
- `pagination.rs`
- `errors.rs` API error payload schema

## 2) Dependencies between issues

Foundation:
- #1 workspace scaffold is prerequisite for all
- #2 local Docker compose enables API/web/db service startup
- #3 DB + migration framework is prerequisite for all model/API work
- #4 Tailwind setup is prerequisite for UI-heavy admin/public pages

Auth chain:
- #5 admin model/seed -> #6 login JWT -> #7 auth middleware -> #8 admin login page

Taxonomy chain:
- #9 category/tag schema -> #10 category CRUD + #11 tag CRUD -> #12 admin management pages

Media chain:
- #13 S3 client/service -> #14 upload endpoint -> #15 frontend upload component

Post chain:
- #16 post schema (FK to categories/tags, image refs) -> #17 post CRUD -> #18 list/delete -> #19 create/edit form

Public site chain:
- #20 public read APIs -> #21 homepage pagination -> #22 post detail markdown -> #23 category/tag filtering

Hardening/finalization:
- #24 integration tests should cover #6, #7, #10, #11, #17, #20
- #25 global error handling + validation ideally introduced early but finalized after core endpoints exist
- #26 production Dockerfiles/deploy config after app behavior is stable

## 3) Key design decisions

- Use a layered backend (`handler -> service -> repository`) for testability and stable API contracts.
- Use typed DTOs in `crates/shared` to reduce API/frontend drift.
- Prefer stateless JWT auth with short-lived access token; middleware injects authenticated admin context.
- Use migration-first schema evolution; every model/API issue includes migration updates.
- Keep uploads metadata in DB and binary objects in S3-compatible storage.
- Standardize list endpoints around pagination/filter query structs from shared crate.
- Centralize error and validation responses to enforce one JSON error contract.
- Keep frontend pages thin: page-level data loading + reusable form/list/upload components.
- Build CRUD endpoints with consistent route conventions to simplify integration tests.
